About Bongo : 
Bongo owned and managed by BONGO HOLDINGS PTE LTD, is the first and biggest streaming video-on-demand service in Bangladesh. Bongo boasts an ever-growing library of over 15.000 full movies, dubbed movies, dramas, TV shows, music videos and songs. This unique collection of Bangladeshi content is available through our website, mobile app and other syndicated video delivery media. Bongo has already been recognized with a top start-up in Bangladesh award and has received acclaim from Silicon Valley and European-based investment.

Bongo is the first online video service in Bangladesh to be actively involved in creating original content. Our aim is to publish a new episode of original creative content every day, for our wide audience.

Apart from Bongo Originals, our library contains aggregated content from some of the biggest Labels and TV Channels in Bangladesh. All their content will be available on Bongo including all new releases.

We are Sealcentre Pieterburen, one of the oldest and largest seal rescue centers in the world. For years we have a passion for seals and their environment. A clean and healthy Wadden Sea is very dear to us. This unique piece of nature has the status UNESCO World heritage and we should treat it accordingly; for now, for later and for our children.
On our campus and field station live and work volunteers and researchers from all over the world. By our collective passion and multidisciplinary approach we form a learning community. We transfer our knowledge and passion to the public and make them aware of our mission.
All seals at the Sealcentre are wild animals and none of them is held in captivity. All seals are released again into their natural environment after their period of rehabilitation.

Science gets a bad rep for being boring, difficult and for very smart people (see: nerds). But that doesn't have to be the case. At ScienceABC we believe that if science is communicated simply and made relatable and fun, it can be for everyone. As Micheal Jackson said best, "as simple as ABC."

So far, we've tackled complex and vast topics like Einstein's Time Dilation, the Immune System, Evolution, Quantum Entanglement, while also asking the questions that nag us at night like "Is the science in the movies accurate?", "Is it possible to have insects the size of humans?", and "Why can I hear a thundering sound in my ear?"

Synod Information & Publicity (Synfo)
The Synod Information & Publicity Department was started in 2002. It is a Sub-Committee under the Synod Executive Committee and is headed by an Executive Secretary. The main functions of the Department are:
1. To collect news form various departments of the Synod and to publicise it
2. To maintain the official website of the Mizoram Synod
3. Audio-Visual Productions, etc.
It publishes a weekly updated news bulletin Synfocity for the local media and sends out the same to a number of recipients by E-mail. It also supplies News in pictures and Sermon-Videos to the local TV Operators. The Department covers all the important conferences/ meetings/functions under the Synod with video for publicity and archives.
